From 91c3d2019fae47c3fc81ade58daf5dfa1f64c174 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arun Vikas T <vikast@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2025 22:06:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:CP:HOSTAPD Register to receive Robust
 AV SCS action frame

Add support for registering the Robust AV SCS (Stream Classification
Service) request action frame with the nl80211 driver interface.

Enable hostapd to recognize and handle SCS action frames, which are
used to support enhanced QoS classification and prioritization for
AV traffic in wireless networks.

Patch-dependency: None
Patch-work:
https://lore.kernel.org/all/20250624205716.1052329-1-quic_rchoodam@quicinc.com/#r
Tag: SCS

Signed-off-by: Arun Vikas T <vikast@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c b/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
index d27a13f..45ee087 100644
--- a/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
+++ b/src/drivers/driver_nl80211.c
@@ -2830,6 +2830,11 @@ static int nl80211_action_subscribe_ap(struct i802_bss *bss)
 	if (nl80211_register_action_frame(bss, (u8 *) "\x12", 1) < 0)
 		ret = -1;
 #endif /* CONFIG_FST */
+#ifdef CONFIG_IEEE80211AX
+	/* Robust AV SCS request */
+	if (nl80211_register_action_frame(bss, (u8 *) "\x13\x00", 1) < 0)
+		ret = -1;
+#endif /* CONFIG_IEEE80211AX */
 #ifdef CONFIG_IEEE80211BE
 	/* Protected EHT Action frames */
 	if (nl80211_register_action_frame(bss, (u8 *) "\x25", 1) < 0)
-- 
